      <div id="overview">
        <p class="lead">
          Thank you for your interest in our study!<br><br>
          This study is divided in <span class="note">two parts</span>.
        </p>
        <ol>
          <!-- This is the real one (mentioning the 1 minutes waiting time)-->
          <li>
            <p>In the <span class="note">first part, a group decision-making game</span>, you will be asked to make a series of choices with other participants (i.e. teammates). Based on these decisions, your team will be able to earn some <span class="note">bonus</span> that will be added to your participation fee.</p>
            <p>This part of the study will be <span class="note">played in groups</span> with other study participants. <span class="note">In order to find enough participants (2 to 10 people)</span>, you might need to wait for up to <span class="note">2&nbsp;minutes</span> to begin with this part of the study. Do not worry about losing time during this process and please be patient: <span class="note">You will be paid for the amount of time you have waited</span> and still attended to our study (10&nbsp;pence per minute)!</p>
          </li>
          <!-- This is the pilot one (individual condition only, therefore only 30 seconds waiting time)-->
          <!--<li>
            In the first part, you will be asked to make a number of decisions and you can earn an additional bonus based on your choices. You may have to wait for up to 10&nbsp;seconds to begin the task in a waiting screen. Do not worry about losing your waiting time: You will be paid for the amount of time you wait (10&nbsp;pence per minute)!
          </li>-->
          <li>
           In the <span class="note">second part</span> of the study, you will be asked to fill out a short survey. This survey will help us to understand how you decided in part one. All results will be <span class="note">collected fully confidentially</span>.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <br />
        <p class="lead">
         Upon completion of the study, you will be paid <span class="note">1&nbsp;pound sterling for your completion</span>, plus any extra bonus you earned both in the waiting room and in the first part of the study (roughly up to 3 pound sterling). The completion of the study should take about 15 minutes.
        </p>
