      <h2>What will happen to me if I take part?</h2>
        <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
          If you decide to take part in this study, you first have to confirm your willingness to do so. After your declaration of consent, you will be asked to complete the decision-making game and the survey. Finally, you have to submit the study for a successful participation. You are free to withdraw from this study at any time and without giving a reason.
        </p>

      <h2>Are there any risks or side effects?</h2>
      <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
        The task is fully anonymous and there are no possible disadvantages or risks of taking part.
      </p>

      <h2>What do I have to do?</h2>
      <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
        In the first part, you will have to make a series of binary choices. The survey part consists of some demographic information (such as age and gender) and other questions to measure your thoughts on the specific task at hand. The entire study (including both the game and the survey) will take approximately 15 minutes to complete.
      </p>

      <h2>What are the possible benefits of taking part?</h2>
      <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
        The decision-making game will earn you some extra bonus rewards in addition to the flat fee for completing the study. The more points you collect during the game, the more bonus you earn!
      </p>

      <h2>What information about me will be held?</h2>
      <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
        We will keep a record of your results of the completed game and the survey. The results will be stored on a computer at the University of Konstanz for analysis purposes. All information which is collected about you during the course of the study will stay strictly confidential. The data that you provide will be only connected to your PROLIFIC_ID and anonymised at the earliest point in data analysis. That is, after completion and compensation, the ID will be deleted from the dataset. Your anonymised data will only be associated with the demographic information you provide at the end of the questionnaire. Once anonymised, we will not be able to delete your data. While the anonymised data might be made available on a public data repository for scientific purposes only, the lead researcher, Dr Wataru Toyokawa, will be in charge of ensuring that the security and confidentiality of your information is maintained.
      </p>

      <h2>What will happen to the results of the research study?</h2>
      <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
        The data will be analysed and published in scientific journals and presented at scientific conferences. Any information that could identify you will not be published.
      </p>

      <h2>Who is organising and funding the research?</h2>
      <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
        This research is being conducted by members of the Social Psychology and Decision Sciences, Department of Psychology, University of Konstanz, Konstanz, Germany. This research is financially supported by the Committee on Research (AFF) of the University of Konstanz (16903119 FP 031/19).  
      </p>

